obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4493)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Contingency Fund of India Act, 1950.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632&sectionId=4493&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4494)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Establishment of the Contingency Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632&sectionId=4494&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] There shall be established a Contingency Fund in the nature of an impress entitled the Contingency Fund of India, into which shall be paid from and out of the Consolidated Fund of India a sum of ^2[fifty crores of rupees.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) On and from the date on which the Finance Bill, 2005 receives the assent of the president, the sum which shall be paid from and out of the Consolidated Fund of India into the Contingency Fund of India under sub-section (1) shall stand enhanced to five hundred crores of rupees.]`
  line
  line `^4[(3) On and from the date on which the Finance Bill, 2021 receives the assent of the President, the sum which shall be paid from and out of the Consolidated Fund of India into the Contingency Fund of India under sub-section (2) shall stand enhanced to thirty thousand crores of rupees.]`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that during the period beginning on the 28th day of July, 1999 and ending on the 31st day of March, 2000, this section shall have effect subject to the modification that for the words “fifty crores of rupees”, the words “five hundred and fifty crores of rupees” shall be substituted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that during the period beginning on the 24th day of January, 1998 and ending on the 31st day of March, 1998, this section shall have effect subject to the modification that for the words “fifty crores of rupees”, the words “thirty-two thousand four hundred and ninety crores of rupees” shall be substituted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 2 numbered as sub-section (1) by Act 18 of 2005, s. 115 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 81 of 1976 “thirty crores of rupees” (w.e.f 26-8-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s. 115 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 127 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1998, s. 2 “for Proviso” (w.e.f. 26-12-1997).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4495)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Custody of the Contingency Fund and withdrawals therefrom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632&sectionId=4495&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Contingency Fund of`
  line `India shall be held on behalf of the President by a Secretary to the Government of India in the`
  line `Ministry of Finance, and no advances shall be made out of such fund except for the purposes of`
  line `meeting unforeseen expenditure pending authorisation of such expenditure by Parliament under`
  line `appropriations made by law.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4496)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632&sectionId=4496&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00038_195049_1517807324632
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] For the purpose of carrying out the objects of this Act, the`
  line `Central Government may, 6`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules regulating all matters`
  line `connected with or ancillary to the custody of, the payment of moneys into and the withdrawal of`
  line `moneys from, the Contingency Fund of India.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 4 renumbered as sub-section (1) by Act 51 of 1982, s. 2 (w.e.f 20-10-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f 20-10-1982).`
